==German==
===Etymology===
Old High German ''kalt'', Old Saxon ''kald''
===Adjective===
'''kalt''' (''comparative'' [[kälter]], ''superlative'' [[kältest]])

# [[cold]]
# [[calm]], [[restrained]], [[passionless]]

====Phrases====
* '''kalt bleiben''' - keep one's temper
* '''kalten Blutes''' - in cold blood
* '''kalter Brand''' - [[gangrene]]
* '''kaltes Fieber''' - [[ague]]

